      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TRUNKEY VILLAIN (1) slotted in just off the lead from the wide draw last start and boxed on to finish third (26.39) at Bulli in a Grade 4/5 over 472m. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Well placed and gets his chance. ZIPPING CRUELLA (6) goes very well at the course with four wins and a placing from six starts. Missed the frame latest (30.52) when sixth over 520m at Wentworth Park in a Grade 5. Looks well placed here and among the chances. TEMORA TERROR (2) was in the money again last time and not beaten far when second (32.74) at Temora in a Grade 5. Can improve sharply here. IT'S ALL BAD (7) placed last time as favourite - worth some thought.",
